<ul class="task-constraints">
<li><b>Time limit:</b> 1.00 s</li>
<li><b>Memory limit:</b> 512 MB</li>
</ul>
<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="2075">
You have an array that contains a permutation of integers $1,2,\dots,n$. Your task is to sort the array in increasing order by reversing subarrays. You can construct any solution that has at most $n$ reversals.<br />
<br />
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The first input line has an integer $n$: the size of the array. The array elements are numbered $1,2,\dots,n$.<br />
<br />
The next line has $n$ integers $x_1,x_2,\dots,x_n$: the contents of the array.<br />
<br />
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
First print an integer $k$: the number of reversals.<br />
<br />
After that, print $k$ lines that describe the reversals. Each line has two integers $a$ and $b$: you reverse a subarray from position $a$ to position $b$.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li>$1 \le n \le 2 \cdot 10^5$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>4<br />
2 3 1 4</code><br />
<br />
Output:<br />
<code>2<br />
1 3<br />
2 3</code>    </div>
